There was sympathetic weakness throughout the entire list of Continentals, Belgian francis losing approximately 10 points at 5.35 cents and dire selling down to 4.73 cents as compared with 4.74 1/2 cents on the previous day.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Certain-teed Products Corporation for the year ended Dec. 31, 1922, reports gross income of $3,464.323, against $3,642,050 in the previous year. Net profits, after all expenses, including reserves for taxes, amounted to $672,015, against $398,397 in 1921. The balance available for dividends amounted to $671,793, against $415,114, and the surplus after dividends was $234,643, against $16,114.

headline.main: CERTAIN-TEED SALES MAKE HIGH RECORD; Report for Year Shows Net Profits of $672,015, Against $398,397 in 1921.
